<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1853" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1853">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President of Venezuela</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am delighted to learn that Secretary Knox was received with such marked
                            cordiality in Venezuela and to assure Your Excellency of my fervent
                            hopes for your continued prosperity and that of Venezuela.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>